"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-12-12-Paris-2024-organizers-claim-event-far-less-polluting-than-recent-Games-1zhbjSKZrgY-p.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can change your cookie settings through your browser.\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CGTN  Copied  The Paris Olympics says it was far less polluting than recent Games but is not claiming to have been \\\"carbon neutral\\\" despite funding projects to compensate for its emissions.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 223, \"end\": 237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers said Wednesday that this summer's Olympics and Paralympics generated 1.44 million tonnes of climate-warming carbon dioxide, from the food athletes ate and construction of their rooms to flights that spectators took and energy that powered events.\", \"from\": 396, \"to\": 653, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to a French government carbon-impact calculator, 1.44 million tonnes of CO2 is equivalent to driving a car 182,675 times around the globe or 898,305 return flights between Paris and New York.\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 856, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 837, \"end\": 842, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2144553943510378e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 847, \"end\": 855, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 0.999999981997462, \"rank\": 1.6953161736991322e-08, \"text\": \"New York\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, Paris Games organizers said they more than met their goal of slashing the Olympics' pollution footprint by half - announcing a 54.6 percent reduction in CO2 emissions compared to the London Olympics in 2012 and the Rio de Janeiro Games in 2016.\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 1109, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 865, \"end\": 870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2144553943510378e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1048, \"end\": 1063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.131190255201055e-14, \"text\": \"London Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1080, \"end\": 1094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4712342746702816e-17, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Workers remove grandstand seating as part of the dismantling of the Olympic venue the \\\"Stade Tour Eiffel\\\" in Paris, France, September 13, 2024.\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1254, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1220, \"end\": 1225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2144553943510378e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1227, \"end\": 1233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999966803471201, \"rank\": 3.014595525492965e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP  Paris organizers said thinking about carbon emissions far in advance of the Games and setting a reduction target were key.\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1383, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1261, \"end\": 1266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2144553943510378e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those who led the task of planning and organizing the mega-event were given carbon budgets.\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1475, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Measures to slash emissions were built into plans from the start.\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just as athletes seek ways to shave milliseconds off their times, Paris organizers sought not just big carbon savings by building just one competition venue specifically for the Games, but smaller ones, too.\", \"from\": 1543, \"to\": 1750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1609, \"end\": 1614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2144553943510378e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic cauldron used electricity and LED spotlights to give the impression of being ablaze.\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1848, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That made it 300 times less polluting than if it had burned gas.\", \"from\": 1849, \"to\": 1913, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even Olympic medals included recycled materials, with each embedded with a reused chunk of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 2022, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Electricity powered 98.4 percent of the Games' energy needs, and organizers said a purchasing agreement they signed with power supplier EDF ensured it was all solar- or wind-generated.\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2208, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Plant-based hot dogs and other vegetarian offerings less carbon-intensive than meat dishes accounted for 40 percent of the food that spectators ate, and the carbon footprint of meals served to Games workers and volunteers was half that of the typical French meal, organizers said.\", \"from\": 2210, \"to\": 2490, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A tourist boat navigates on the Seine after the first triathlon training session was canceled due to the pollution of the river during the Paris 2024 Olympic Games in Paris, France, July 28, 2024.\", \"from\": 2492, \"to\": 2688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2524, \"end\": 2529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999965933301429, \"rank\": 3.4013629255407634e-06, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 2659, \"end\": 2664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2144553943510378e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2666, \"end\": 2672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999966803471201, \"rank\": 3.014595525492965e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP  In selling 12.1 million tickets, Paris set attendance records.\", \"from\": 2689, \"to\": 2757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2728, \"end\": 2733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2144553943510378e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But transporting spectators to the French capital and to events came at an unexpectedly large carbon cost.\", \"from\": 2758, \"to\": 2864, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Transport had been expected to account for about one-third of Paris' carbon footprint, but organizers said it ended up accounting for 53 percent.\", \"from\": 2865, \"to\": 3010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2927, \"end\": 2932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2144553943510378e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just over 66 percent of spectators came from France.\", \"from\": 3012, \"to\": 3064, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3057, \"end\": 3063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999966803471201, \"rank\": 3.014595525492965e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 21 percent came from elsewhere in Europe, and another 12 percent came from further afield, led by ticket-holders from the United States, Brazil and Canada.\", \"from\": 3065, \"to\": 3230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3197, \"end\": 3210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999989186627707, \"rank\": 1.0813383137648338e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3212, \"end\": 3218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"score\": 0.9999999811161617, \"rank\": 9.949993135360328e-09, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\"}, {\"begin\": 3223, \"end\": 3229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999503593257, \"rank\": 4.96316550766377e-08, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For spectators who took long-haul flights, the carbon impact was about 1,000 times greater than transporting those from the Paris region.\", \"from\": 3231, \"to\": 3368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3355, \"end\": 3360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2144553943510378e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The illuminated Eiffel Tower in Paris, France, July 26, 2024.\", \"from\": 3370, \"to\": 3431, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3402, \"end\": 3407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2144553943510378e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3409, \"end\": 3415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999966803471201, \"rank\": 3.014595525492965e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP  Organizers said they are spending just over 12 million euros ($12.6 million) on projects in Africa, Asia, Central America and France that aim to compensate for the Games' 1.44 million tonnes of carbon emissions.\", \"from\": 3432, \"to\": 3649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3564, \"end\": 3570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999966803471201, \"rank\": 3.014595525492965e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The money is funding tens of thousands of less-polluting cooking stoves and access to water in Nigeria, Congo, Kenya and Rwanda, solar power in Senegal and Vietnam and forestation in Guatemala, Kenya, Senegal and France, organizers said.\", \"from\": 3651, \"to\": 3888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3746, \"end\": 3753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9999992088754371, \"rank\": 7.907375183684332e-07, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}, {\"begin\": 3755, \"end\": 3760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo\", \"score\": 0.973566713432254, \"rank\": 0.023470682270165237, \"text\": \"Congo\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo\"}, {\"begin\": 3762, \"end\": 3767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.7701934002233528e-12, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 3772, \"end\": 3778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rwanda\", \"score\": 0.9999999867250154, \"rank\": 1.0441140766556852e-08, \"text\": \"Rwanda\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rwanda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rwanda\"}, {\"begin\": 3795, \"end\": 3802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senegal\", \"score\": 0.9999999997321538, \"rank\": 2.516573810296733e-10, \"text\": \"Senegal\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senegal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senegal\"}, {\"begin\": 3807, \"end\": 3814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vietnam\", \"score\": 0.9896859942959648, \"rank\": 0.010420921626969611, \"text\": \"Vietnam\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vietnam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vietnam\"}, {\"begin\": 3834, \"end\": 3843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\", \"score\": 0.9999879541808433, \"rank\": 1.204561011615529e-05, \"text\": \"Guatemala\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\"}, {\"begin\": 3845, \"end\": 3850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.7701934002233528e-12, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 3852, \"end\": 3859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senegal\", \"score\": 0.9999999997321538, \"rank\": 2.516573810296733e-10, \"text\": \"Senegal\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senegal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Senegal\"}, {\"begin\": 3864, \"end\": 3870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999966803471201, \"rank\": 3.014595525492965e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Cover: A gaggle of Canadian geese take off at Vaires-sur-Marne Nautical Stadium in Vaires-sur-Marne, France, August 10, 2024.\", \"from\": 3890, \"to\": 4016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3910, \"end\": 3924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.o